Apart from golf, perhaps the only other thing all 12 European players plus their captain Paul McGinley have in common is a love of football. 

So you can imagine the reaction when Sir Alex Ferguson walked into the team room at Gleneagles last evening.

It didn’t matter, of course, that only two of them supported Manchester United; that rival clubs including Liverpool, Arsenal, Real Madrid and Bayern Munich all had their supporters.  

